Class Description
ASet
An ASet is an unordered set of vertices used in the Dijkstra algorithm to keep track of the already visited vertices.
Box
This abstract class implements a graph's vertex.
BoxFlag
This enumerated type describes a set of flags carried by a Box instance.

CommandInterface
Interfaces a command callable by a user interface.
Dijkstra
The Dijkstra algorithm is applied to a graph given a vertex called root.
DIJKSTRA_Dijkstra
Dijkstra command runs dijkstra algorithm on a given maze.
DIJKSTRA_TracePath
TracePath command marks the path calculated by dijkstra to a given vertex
DISPLAY_DisplayMaze
DisplayMaze displays the maze in an output stream.
DISPLAY_DrawMaze
DrawMaze draws the maze in a tile map.
DISPLAY_HideFlag
HideFlag requires the maze to hide a flag when displaying.
DISPLAY_HideFlags
HideFlags requires maze to hide all flags when displaying.
DISPLAY_ShowFlag
ShowFlag requires maze to show a flag when displaying.
DISPLAY_ShowFlags
ShowFlags requires maze to show all flags when displaying.

EDIT_AddCol

EDIT_AddFlag

EDIT_AddRow

EDIT_Clear

EDIT_RemBox

EDIT_RemCol

EDIT_RemFlag
Removes a flag at given coordinates.
EDIT_RemRoot
RemRoot removes the current root in maze.
EDIT_RemRow
RemRow removes a row in the maze at a given position.
EDIT_SetRoot
SetRoot sets a new root in the maze.
EmptyBox

Graph
A graph is an ordered set of vertices, linked by distances to one another.

IO_OpenMaze

IO_SaveMaze

NullBoxException

Pi

PiFunction

Previous
